The evidence with the title 'Trauma in the er: who pays for the uninsured? | National News ... ' says Jun 20, 2012  ... If the law is upheld , millions of newly insured patients will have many of their hospital bills covered by insurance . But if the law, or just the insurance mandate, is struck down , those bills will be passed on to taxpayers, hospitals and privately insured patients , as they have been for the past quarter-century. 
